dmca.title: E-mail on behalf of C.W. Arnett regarding www.tadalafilo.com
dmca.body:
-----Original Message-----
From: DeOrto, Heather J. [mailto:Heather.DeOrto@bakerd.com] 
Posted At: Thursday, August 03, 2006 11:48 AM
Posted To: Legal Response
Conversation: E-mail on behalf of C.W. Arnett regarding
www.tadalafilo.com
Subject: E-mail on behalf of C.W. Arnett regarding www.tadalafilo.com



Attn:  Legal Response Team
The Planet.com Internet Services, Inc.

Re:  Trademark Complaint from Cialis tadalafilo.com

Gentlemen:

We are in receipt of and thank you for your timely response to our
complaint on behalf of Lilly ICOS in connection with the website
www.tadalafilo.com.

We note that the copyright-protected brand packaging has been removed
from the site, however the site continues to display a tablet which is
confusingly similar to the trademark-protected CIALIS tablet.  We
request that you remove or disable access to this material as well.

Please contact me if you have any questions. 



Very truly yours,



Charles W. Arnett

C.W. Arnett
cw.arnett@bakerd.com
Ph. 317-237-1401

300 North Meridian Street, Suite 2700
Indianapolis, IN 46204
317.237.0300 (Main)
317.237.1000 (Fax)
www.bakerdaniels.com

Indiana  |  Washington, D.C.  |  China



t

-----Original Message-----
From: legal-response@theplanet.com [mailto:legal-response@theplanet.com]

Sent: Thursday, June 15, 2006 5:37 PM
To: Arnett, Charles W.; copyright@theplanet.com
Subject: Trademark Complaint from Cialis tadalafilo.com


To Whom It May Concern:



This letter confirms that access to the materials referenced in your
below-pasted complaint has been disabled.



Legal Response Team

The Planet




---------


Please see attached.



--------------------------------------------
ATTENTION: 


To ensure compliance with applicable Internal Revenue Service
Regulations,

we inform you that any tax advice contained in this electronic message
was

not intended or written to be used, and cannot be used, for the purpose
of

avoiding penalties under the Internal Revenue Code.

This message and all attachments are PRIVATE, and may contain
information that is CONFIDENTIAL and PRIVILEGED. 

If you received this message in error, please notify the sender by reply

e-mail and delete the message immediately.
